comments: Sharpe (POR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Thybulle (POR) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Gobert (MIN) jumps alongside Mays (POR) and maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Mays' (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as they briefly come together during the screen.
Knox II (POR) briefly engages and immediately disengages with Gobert (MIN) as marginal contact occurs when he goes under the pick.
Thybulle (POR) establishes himself in Edwards' (MIN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Thybulle (POR) brings his hands toward Edwards (MIN) and marginal contact occurs as Thybulle (POR) releases away to roll.
Edwards (MIN) reaches across and initiates contact with Sharpe's (POR) arms, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Thybulle's (POR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Thybulle (POR) reaches in and makes contact with Edwards' (MIN) arm during his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Sharpe (POR) brings his hands toward McDaniels (MIN) and marginal contact occurs as Sharpe (POR) releases away to the perimeter.
Eubanks (POR) establishes himself in McDaniels' (MIN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Gobert (MIN) immediately removes his collapsed forearm from Sharpe's (POR) shoulder as he absorbs the marginal contact during his contest on the driving shot attempt.
Knox II (POR) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Edwards (MIN) establishes himself in Knox II's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the screen.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Edwards (MIN) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Edwards (MIN) was the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and possession correctly remains with the Trail Blazers.
Edwards (MIN) and Knox II (POR) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
During the inbound, McDaniels (MIN) runs alongside Sharpe (POR) and marginal contact occurs as Sharpe slips and stumbles on his own.
Gobert (MIN) initiates contact with Eubanks' (POR) arm, which affects Eubanks' SQBR.

Mays (POR) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Anderson's (MIN) arm after the release. Any follow-through contact with Knox II (POR) after Anderson returns to the floor is deemed incidental.
Anderson's (MIN) shot attempt touches the shot clock and basket wiring out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the Trail Blazers.

Knox II (POR) does not bring his back leg over the midcourt line, he maintains his status in the backcourt. To establish front court possession you need to bring the ball and both legs across the midcourt line.
